@@TJvScrollBar
<TITLEIMG TJvScrollBar>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.GridsAndContent.Scrollbars
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Supports extended features such as hot tracking.
Description
  TJvScrollBar is a scroll bar that supports extended features such as hot tracking. It adds
  four events to TScrollBar: OnCtl3DChanged, OnParentColorChange, OnMouseEnter and OnMouseLeave.

  Use OnMouseEnter and OnMouseLeave to alter the controls look or behavoir, when the user moves the
  mouse pointer over the control.

  Alternatively, you could use property HotTrack to highlight the scroll bar automatically when the
  mouse passes over it.

  Property HintColor can be used to set a different color of the Help hint boxes for the scroll bar.

  A TJvScrollBar scroll bar can contain objects, such as TButton and TLabel objects.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollBar.Create
Summary
  Creates and initializes an instance of TJvScrollBar.
Description
  Call \Create to create an instance of TJvScrollBar at runtime. A TJvScrollBar component placed on a
  form at design time is created automatically.

  Pass a single Component as a parameter to provide the scroll bar with an Owner that is responsible
  for freeing it.

  \Create calls the inherited \Create method, then sets the initial values for the scroll bar as follows:

  * HintColor is set to clInfoBk.
  * HotTrack is set to False.
  * csAcceptsControls is added to ControlStyle.
Parameters
  AOwner - The owner for the instance of TJvScrollbar.
See Also
  HintColor, HotTrack, OnCtl3DChanged, OnMouseEnter, OnMouseLeave, OnParentColorChange
